description:
I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I suspect it may be related to a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler. To reproduce the issue, create a class in a subpackage, like this:

```java
package subpackage;

public class Test {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		System.out.println("Hello");
	}
}
```

Then compile using the following command:

```
ajc subpackage\Test.java
```

You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory. The same command with javac, `javac subpackage\Test.java`, does not have this issue. It's not a major problem, but it's an unexpected behavior.
